bug.short_desc: There are two shotwell icons on the desktop.
bug.cf_doc_type: If docs needed, set a value

long_desc.thetext:
Created attachment 1186154 Two "shotwells" on the desktop
Description of problem: A recent update of shotwell brought two shotwell desktop icons on the desktop.
Version-Release number of selected component (if applicable): 0.23.4
How reproducible: Always
Steps to Reproduce: (not sure what exact steps to follow) 1.Upgrade shotwell to 0.23.4 if you were using an older version. 2. 3.
Actual results: There are two shotwell icons on the desktop.
Expected results: There should be only one as it is normal for apps.
Additional info: Both "shotwells" are the same program.

I have the same problem. There seems to be a bug in one of the .desktop files. /usr/share/applications/shotwell-viewer.desktop is missing the 'NoDisplay=true' entry which was present in earlier versions.

This issue has been fixed upstream;
https://git.gnome.org/browse/shotwell/commit/?id=255a39c9e5c9df94bc16f2988ac50f9bc6dd9866
